"{\"uid\": \"rappler.com-sports-football-new-zealand-reports-canada-2024-paris-olympics-committee-drone-incident\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  SUMMARY  This is AI generated summarization, which may have errors.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 69, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19, \"end\": 21, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999995479421271, \"rank\": 3.1022907280697307e-07, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For context, always refer to the full article.\", \"from\": 70, \"to\": 116, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"OLYMPIC SITES.\", \"from\": 118, \"to\": 132, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic rings, French and European Union flags, at the 2024 Paris Olympics international broadcast centre at Parc des Expositions.\", \"from\": 133, \"to\": 267, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 152, \"end\": 158, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9806352327298758, \"rank\": 0.011674946581338445, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 163, \"end\": 177, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\", \"score\": 0.9999999140570744, \"rank\": 8.591950232108052e-08, \"text\": \"European Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\"}, {\"begin\": 172, \"end\": 177, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999998428802551, \"rank\": 1.565579470826054e-07, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 246, \"end\": 266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_Expo_Porte_de_Versailles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.510043065915967e-21, \"text\": \"Parc des Expositions\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_Expo_Porte_de_Versailles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_Expo_Porte_de_Versailles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kirby Lee/USA TODAY Sports/Reuters  PARIS, France - New Zealand's Olympic Committee says its women's soccer team had their training session disrupted by a drone flown by a staff member of the Canadian team they face in Group A on Thursday, July 25.\", \"from\": 269, \"to\": 517, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 269, \"end\": 274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Kirby\", \"score\": 0.9976139746095182, \"rank\": 0.0023890878209221495, \"text\": \"Kirby\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Kirby\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Kirby\"}, {\"begin\": 275, \"end\": 278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\", \"score\": 0.9978631531294205, \"rank\": 0.0021414226412526578, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\"}, {\"begin\": 279, \"end\": 288, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Today\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USA TODAY\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Today\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Today\"}, {\"begin\": 312, \"end\": 318, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9449162164602319, \"rank\": 0.0458786339497167, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 321, \"end\": 332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.6289330322083937, \"rank\": 0.4305631647530616, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 461, \"end\": 469, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9446026361710635, \"rank\": 0.05859368963419708, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 488, \"end\": 495, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_A\", \"score\": 0.9880433631422867, \"rank\": 0.012101233640341245, \"text\": \"Group A\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_A\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_A\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"On July 22, a drone was flown over the New Zealand women's football team training session in St Etienne,\\\" the NZOC said on Tuesday, July 23.\", \"from\": 519, \"to\": 660, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 559, \"end\": 570, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.6289330322083937, \"rank\": 0.4305631647530616, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 613, \"end\": 623, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Stephen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7673101669225152e-15, \"text\": \"St Etienne\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Stephen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Stephen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Team support members immediately reported the incident to police, leading to the drone operator, who has been identified as a support staff member of the wider Canadian Women's football team, to be detained.\\\"\", \"from\": 662, \"to\": 871, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 823, \"end\": 831, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9446026361710635, \"rank\": 0.05859368963419708, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The incident was immediately reported to the International Olympic Committee's integrity unit and Team Canada has since apologized and is said to be investigating, the NZOC said.\", \"from\": 873, \"to\": 1051, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 918, \"end\": 949, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 971, \"end\": 982, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hockey_Canada\", \"score\": 0.8172691928845108, \"rank\": 0.22358703696134366, \"text\": \"Team Canada\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hockey_Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hockey_Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The NZOC and New Zealand Football are committed to upholding the integrity and fairness of the Olympic Games and are deeply shocked and disappointed by this incident, which occurred just three days before the sides are due to face each other in their opening game of Paris 2024,\\\" the statement said.\", \"from\": 1053, \"to\": 1353, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1067, \"end\": 1087, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_Football\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"New Zealand Football\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_Football\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_Football\"}, {\"begin\": 1321, \"end\": 1331, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.878321079271131e-18, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"At this time the NZOC's main priority is to support the New Zealand women's football athletes and wider team as they start their campaign.\\\"\", \"from\": 1355, \"to\": 1495, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1412, \"end\": 1423, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.6289330322083937, \"rank\": 0.4305631647530616, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Canadian Olympic Committee said they were informed of the incident involving \\\"a non-accredited member of the Canada Soccer support team,\\\" adding that they are \\\"reviewing next steps with the IOC, Paris 2024, Canada Soccer and FIFA.\\\"\", \"from\": 1497, \"to\": 1732, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1501, \"end\": 1527, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Canadian Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1610, \"end\": 1623, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Soccer_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Canada Soccer\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Soccer_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Soccer_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 1691, \"end\": 1694, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2826213538611889e-28, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Canadian Olympic Committee stands for fair-play and we are shocked and disappointed.\", \"from\": 1734, \"to\": 1823, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1739, \"end\": 1765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Canadian Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We offer our heartfelt apologies to New Zealand Football, to all the players affected and to the New Zealand Olympic Committee,\\\" they said in a statement.\", \"from\": 1824, \"to\": 1978, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1860, \"end\": 1880, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_Football\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"New Zealand Football\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_Football\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_Football\"}, {\"begin\": 1921, \"end\": 1950, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"New Zealand Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Wednesday, July 24, the Canadian women's soccer team assistant coach and an analyst have been kicked out of the Olympic squad, the Canadian Olympic Committee (COC) said.\", \"from\": 1980, \"to\": 2152, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2007, \"end\": 2015, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9446026361710635, \"rank\": 0.05859368963419708, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 2114, \"end\": 2140, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Canadian Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2142, \"end\": 2145, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9999999998483418, \"rank\": 1.5161206970111837e-10, \"text\": \"COC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Head coach Bev Priestman has also removed herself from coaching the team against New Zealand in Group A on Thursday, the COC added.\", \"from\": 2154, \"to\": 2285, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2165, \"end\": 2178, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bev_Priestman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bev Priestman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bev_Priestman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bev_Priestman\"}, {\"begin\": 2235, \"end\": 2246, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.6289330322083937, \"rank\": 0.4305631647530616, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2250, \"end\": 2257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_A\", \"score\": 0.9880433631422867, \"rank\": 0.012101233640341245, \"text\": \"Group A\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_A\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_A\"}, {\"begin\": 2275, \"end\": 2278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9999999998483418, \"rank\": 1.5161206970111837e-10, \"text\": \"COC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Joseph Lombardi, an unaccredited analyst with Canada Soccer, is being removed from the Canadian Olympic Team and will be sent home immediately,\\\" COC said in a statement.\", \"from\": 2287, \"to\": 2457, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2288, \"end\": 2294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joseph_Smith\", \"score\": 0.9742539782215166, \"rank\": 0.024676148170389215, \"text\": \"Joseph\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q2566598\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joseph_Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joseph_Smith\"}, {\"begin\": 2334, \"end\": 2347, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Soccer_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Canada Soccer\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Soccer_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Soccer_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 2375, \"end\": 2383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9446026361710635, \"rank\": 0.05859368963419708, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 2433, \"end\": 2436, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9999999998483418, \"rank\": 1.5161206970111837e-10, \"text\": \"COC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Jasmine Mander, an assistant coach to whom Mr. Lombardi reports to, is being removed from the Canadian Olympic Team and will be sent home immediately.\\\"\", \"from\": 2459, \"to\": 2611, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2460, \"end\": 2467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jasmine\", \"score\": 0.9999999095077824, \"rank\": 4.942786564989258e-08, \"text\": \"Jasmine\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jasmine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jasmine\"}, {\"begin\": 2554, \"end\": 2562, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9446026361710635, \"rank\": 0.05859368963419708, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Priestman apologized for the offense.\", \"from\": 2613, \"to\": 2650, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"On behalf of our entire team, I first and foremost want to apologize to the players and staff at New Zealand Football and to the players on Team Canada,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 2652, \"to\": 2816, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2793, \"end\": 2804, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hockey_Canada\", \"score\": 0.8172691928845108, \"rank\": 0.22358703696134366, \"text\": \"Team Canada\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hockey_Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hockey_Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This does not represent the values that our team stands for.\", \"from\": 2818, \"to\": 2879, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am ultimately responsible for conduct in our program.\", \"from\": 2880, \"to\": 2935, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Accordingly, to emphasize our team's commitment to integrity, I have decided to voluntarily withdraw from coaching the match on Thursday.\", \"from\": 2937, \"to\": 3075, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the spirit of accountability, I do this with the interests of both teams in mind and to ensure everyone feels that the sportsmanship of this game is upheld.\\\"\", \"from\": 3076, \"to\": 3236, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"FIFA said on Wednesday it had opened proceedings against Canada Soccer, Priestman, Lombardi, and Mander due to a potential breach\\u00a0of the body's disciplinary code.\", \"from\": 3238, \"to\": 3400, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3238, \"end\": 3242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\", \"score\": 0.999999999772399, \"rank\": 2.2415697818407364e-10, \"text\": \"FIFA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\"}, {\"begin\": 3295, \"end\": 3308, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Soccer_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Canada Soccer\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Soccer_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Soccer_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The matter will be submitted for the consideration of the Disciplinary Committee in the next days,\\\" FIFA\\u00a0said in\\u00a0a statement.\", \"from\": 3402, \"to\": 3528, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Canada Soccer also said on Wednesday it would launch an independent external review that will not only address the circumstances of the matter but also look into the historical culture of competitive ethics within all of its programs.\", \"from\": 3530, \"to\": 3764, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3530, \"end\": 3543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Soccer_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Canada Soccer\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Soccer_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Soccer_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Canada Soccer has always sought to prioritize integrity and fair competition, and we understand that competing with honesty is a baseline expectation for all Canadians,\\\" Canada Soccer President Peter Augruso and CEO Kevin Blue said in a statement.\", \"from\": 3766, \"to\": 4014, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We failed to meet those expectations in this case, and for that, we apologize.\", \"from\": 4016, \"to\": 4095, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"- Rappler.com    How does this make you feel?\", \"from\": 4095, \"to\": 4141, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"follow us\", \"from\": 4143, \"to\": 4152, \"entities\": []}]}"